Class PartialSheetMusic

java.lang.Object
serverCode.Services.PartialSheetMusic
public class PartialSheetMusic extends Object
The class responsible for finding the appropriate partial sheet music chunks in highlighted search results and sending them back

  • Method Details

    • getHighlightMeasures

      public static void getHighlightMeasures(ReqPartialMusic request, List<Integer> start, List<Integer> end)
      Populates the start and end lists with measure ranges that overlap with the highlighted intervals in the music record contained within the request. This method extracts and parses necessary interval and measure information from the request, identifies matched ranges based on highlight data, and appends the result to the output lists.
      Parameters:
      request - The request object containing source music and highlight data.
      start - A list to populate with the start measures of overlapping ranges.
      end - A list to populate with the end measures of overlapping ranges.

    • getBytesFromHighlight

      public static List<List<Byte>> getBytesFromHighlight(String clumpedHighlight)
      Extracts a list of byte-encoded intervals from a highlight string containing space-separated byte values enclosed within tags. For example, the string "1 2 34 5" would be parsed into: [[1, 2, 3], [4, 5]]
      Parameters:
      clumpedHighlight - The raw highlight string containing tags.
      Returns:
      A list of byte lists, each representing a group of parsed interval values.

      Extracts the string contents found between and tags.
      Parameters:
      text - The string containing HTML-emphasized segments.
      Returns:
      A list of strings, each being the content inside a matched ... block.

    • getMeasuresOfAllPatterns

      public static List<List<Integer>> getMeasuresOfAllPatterns(List<List<Byte>> highlightPatterns, List<Byte> allIntervals, List<Integer> measureNumbers)
      Identifies ranges of measure numbers that correspond to matched highlight sequences. Each matched sequence from highlightPatterns is located within the allIntervals, and its corresponding measure number range is extracted using measureNumbers. Adjacent or overlapping measure ranges are merged into unified intervals.
      Parameters:
      highlightPatterns - A list of byte-sequence patterns to search for.
      allIntervals - The complete list of byte intervals in order.
      measureNumbers - A list of measure numbers mapped one-to-one with allIntervals + 1 element.
      Returns:
      A list of merged measure number intervals represented as two-element lists [start, end].

    • findSubsequencePositions

      public static List<Integer> findSubsequencePositions(List<Byte> main, List<Byte> pattern)
      Finds all starting positions in the main list where the pattern list appears as a contiguous subsequence. The search is performed by converting both lists to space-separated string representations and then locating all occurrences of the pattern within the main string as Java's string search is highly optimized.

      The returned positions correspond to the starting indices in the main list where each match begins.

      Parameters:
      main - the primary list of bytes to search within
      pattern - the byte pattern to search for as a subsequence
      Returns:
      a list of starting indices where pattern occurs in main
      See Also:
      • convertStringIndexToArrayIndex(String, int)

    • convertStringIndexToArrayIndex

      public static int convertStringIndexToArrayIndex(String arrayStr, int index)
      Converts a string index from the space-delimited array string into a list index. The index corresponds to the number of spaces (i.e., list elements) before the given character position.
      Parameters:
      arrayStr - the string representation of the list (e.g., "12 14 1562 0 2 5 3")
      index - the character index within the string
      Returns:
      the corresponding zero-based index in the original list

    • mergeIntervals

      public static List<List<Integer>> mergeIntervals(List<List<Integer>> intervals)
      Merges overlapping or adjacent intervals into consolidated ranges. Each interval is a two-element list representing [start, end].
      Parameters:
      intervals - The list of intervals to merge.
      Returns:
      A new list of merged intervals.

    • getPartial

      public ResPartialSheetMusic getPartial(ReqPartialMusic request)
      Extracts specific segments of MEI sheet music from a file stored in a PostgreSQL database. The segments correspond to the overlapping highlighted measures defined in the request.
      Parameters:
      request - The ReqPartialMusic containing highlight information and file reference.
      Returns:
      A ResPartialSheetMusic object containing either the matched MEI segments or an error message.

    • fetchFileFromDatabase

      public String fetchFileFromDatabase(String fileName)
      Retrieves the MEI file content associated with the specified file name from the PostgreSQL database table public.meiFiles.
      Parameters:
      fileName - The name of the file to fetch.
      Returns:
      The content of the file if found; otherwise, null or a constant error message such as POSTGRE_SQL_JDBC_DRIVER_NOT_FOUND if the JDBC driver is missing.

    • insideRightMeasure

      private boolean insideRightMeasure(List<Integer> start, List<Integer> end, int checkMe, int pos)
      Determines if the given measure number falls within the range defined by the start and end lists at the specified index.
      Parameters:
      start - A list of starting measure numbers.
      end - A list of ending measure numbers.
      checkMe - The measure number to test.
      pos - The index into the start and end lists to compare against.
      Returns:
      true if checkMe lies between start.get(pos) and end.get(pos) (inclusive), false otherwise or if pos is out of bounds.
